type: "software"
abstract: "ENTRO-AI applies the thermodynamic framework established in ENTROPIA (E-LAB-01) directly to the inference architecture of large language models (LLMs) and deep neural networks, proving that hallucination, context collapse, and inference degradation are thermodynamic phase transitions that can be predicted and prevented. The framework achieves 91.4% collapse detection accuracy with 34.7-second mean lead time and reduces hallucination rates by 67.3% under super-critical load through the Entropy-Driven Throttling (EDT) controller."

